In response to criticism from Archbishop Njongonkulu Ndungane, Bathabile Dlamini says it would be inappropriate for her to engage religious leaders in public. CAPE TOWN - In response to criticism from Archbishop Emeritus Njongonkulu Ndungane, Social Development Minister Bathabile Dlamini says it would be inappropriate for her to engage religious leaders in public.Ndungane on Thursday questioned whether government is aware of the implications if social grant recipients are not paid on 1 April.The former Cape Town Archbishop blames the social grant debacle on poor political leadership.Social Development Department spokesperson Lumka Oliphant say: It would be disrespectful for the minister to engage the man of the cloth in the public domain. The Department of Social Development and the minister have a very good relationship. (Edited by Zamangwane Shange)